Vladimir Nabokov





TO: JOHN SELBY1

CC, 1 p.





802 East Seneca Street

Ithaca, N.Y

January 17, 1951

Dear Mr. Selby,

Two years ago you wrote to me about my book but to my regret at that time we did not arrive at an understanding. To-day I am writing you on an entirely different matter which, I hope, will interest you.

I am teaching a course in European Fiction at Cornell University and have selected as a permanent item Flaubert's "Madame Bovary". In September I ordered, for a class of 1